subSubSection.paragraph:
Based on our field investigations, the new species is currently only known from the type locality Wumeng grassland. Only ca. 300 mature individuals were present and the extent of occurrence is estimated to be ca. 5000 m2. The location is not in a protected area and is accessible to casual hikers. According to the guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria (
IUCN 2017
), the species is categorised as Endangered [EN B1abc(iv); C2a(i,ii)] due to its rarity and the threat of disturbance.
